OL,3,CBishop of Rochester says Church
OL,4,Csafeguarding needs 'change in culture'
OL,6,FThe Diocese of Rochester has voted to
OL,7,Fpass a motion of No Confidence in the
OL,8,FArchbishops' Council, as it says
OL,9,Findependent oversight and scrutiny is
OL,10,Fneeded when it comes to safeguarding.
OL,12,FThe Bishop of Rochester has led calls
OL,13,Ffor urgent reform to the Council,
OL,14,Fwhich is the senior governing body of
OL,15,Fthe Church of England.
OL,17,FIt comes following the resignation of
OL,18,Fthe Archbishop of Canterbury, Justin
OL,19,FWelby, after he admitted failures of
OL,20,Fsafeguarding.
